<body id="top">

    <a href="/" class="back-link">📂 Return to Shelf Deck</a>

    <h1>[01-A] SOLOVERSE - CRAZY 8’s</h1>
    <div class="meta-tag">[GAME RULEBOOK] • 👥 Ages 7+, 3-10 Players • v14.0.0</div>

    <!-- INDEX JUMP MATRIX -->
    <div class="toc-box">
        <div class="toc-title">📋 Contents Index Matrix</div>
        <ul class="toc-list">
            <li><a href="#object" class="toc-link">• OBJECT</a></li>
            <li><a href="#setup" class="toc-link">• SETUP</a></li>
            <li><a href="#how-to-play" class="toc-link">• HOW TO PLAY</a></li>
            <li><a href="#victory-conditions" class="toc-link">• VICTORY CONDITIONS</a></li>
            <li><a href="#team-gameplay" class="toc-link">• TEAM GAMEPLAY</a></li>
            <li><a href="#team-trading" class="toc-link">• TEAM GAMEPLAY: TRADING</a></li>
            <li><a href="#team-victory-changes" class="toc-link">• TEAM GAMEPLAY: SPECIAL VICTORY CONDITIONS</a></li>
            <li><a href="#scoring" class="toc-link">• SCORING</a></li>
            <li><a href="#scoring-winning" class="toc-link">• SCORING: WINNING THE GAME</a></li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- OBJECT -->
    <h2 id="object">OBJECT:</h2>
    <div class="rules-box">
        <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; list-style-type: disc;">
            <li>This game follows the Crazy 8’s style of “Card Shedding” play.</li>
            <li>Therefore: Be the first Player to get rid of all your Cards.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: right; margin-top: 10px;">
        <a href="#top" style="color: var(--color-link); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700;">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>

    <!-- SETUP -->
    <h2 id="setup">SETUP:</h2>
    <div class="rules-box">
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1rem;">
            1. As a group choose whether to use the Core Game Extension and any Optional Expansion or Coloured Extension Packs [compare Universal Game Notes: First Play Recommendations].
        </p>
        <div class="note-box" style="margin-top: -5px;">
            <strong>NOTE:</strong> If you have added any optional Expansions, check if they have any Additional Setup Rules.
        </div>

        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            2. Choose who Deals first [alternate the Dealer clockwise after each game].
        </p>

        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            3. As a group, help Shuffle the Deck, then the Dealer Deals Each Player 7 Cards Face-Down [watch out for the Face-Up Trap Class Chaos Cards – return them randomly to the Deck before continuing to Deal].
        </p>

        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            4. Place the remainder of the Cards Face-Down as a Deck.
        </p>

        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            5. Place the Direction Of Play [Blue/Clockwise Side] and the Play To The Side Of The Discards Chaos Cards Face-Up on either side of the Discards, where everyone can see them [Remember to Flip the Direction Of Play Chaos Card it every time a Reverse Effect Activates].
        </p>

        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            6. If using the Core Extension, place Recycle Chaos Card Face-Up next to the Deck and Discards, where all Players can reach it.
        </p>

        <div style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px;">
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 1rem;">
                7. Flip the top Card of the Deck over to begin the Discards:
            </p>
            <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                <li>If any Action Class Cards are turned over at this stage, follow their rules.</li>
                <li>If any Chaos Card is turned over [including if a Trap Class Chaos Card is revealed in doing so], return it randomly to the Deck and Flip another Card.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: right; margin-top: 15px; margin-bottom: 40px;">
        <a href="#top" style="color: var(--color-link); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700;">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>

		<div class="image-container">
			<img 
				src="/assets/images/layouts/hand-shedder-setup.png" 
				alt="Soloverse Deck-Builder Game Setup Grid Diagram" 
				loading="lazy"
			/>
			<div class="image-caption">Figure 1: Grid configuration for the 4 Trade Rows, 4 Tiered Decks, and Chaos Level Stacks.</div>
		</div>

     <!-- HOW TO PLAY -->
    <h2 id="how-to-play">HOW TO PLAY:</h2>
    <div class="rules-box">
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1rem;">
            1. Play starts clockwise from the Dealer. 
        </p>

        <div style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px;">
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 1rem;">
                2. On your turn, you must play a minimum of 1 Card from your Hand by matching it to the Card on top of Discards either by Colour or Symbol, or by playing a Chaos Card [if able].
            </p>
            <div class="note-box">
                <strong>NOTE:</strong> Chaos Cards can affect how many Cards you can play on your turn.
            </div>
        </div>

        <div style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px;">
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 1rem;">
                3. If you don’t have a playable Card, as outlined above, you must Draw a Card from the Deck.
            </p>
            <div style="background: var(--bg-main-box); padding: 12px; border-radius: 8px; font-size: 0.92rem; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent); margin-bottom: 8px;">
                <strong>PICK-UP/PUT-DOWN RULE:</strong> If the Card you picked up is a playable Coloured Card, feel free to play it now. Otherwise, play moves on to the next person.
            </div>
            <div class="note-box" style="border-left-color: #ef4444;">
                <strong>RESTRICTION:</strong> Chaos Cards cannot be played via the Pick-Up/Put-Down Rule [Some exceptions apply, such as the Steal Turn Chaos Card].
            </div>
        </div>

        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            4. You may also choose not to play a playable Card from your Hand [such as keeping a Chaos Card up your sleeve for later]. If so, you must Draw a Card from the Deck. The Pick-Up/Put-Down Rule applies here as well; however, you may not play any other Card from your Hand after Drawing.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: right; margin-top: 10px;">
        <a href="#top" style="color: var(--color-link); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700;">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>

    <!-- VICTORY CONDITIONS -->
    <h2 id="victory-conditions">VICTORY CONDITIONS:</h2>
    <div class="rules-box">
        <!-- RULE 1 -->
        <div style="margin: 0; padding-bottom: 15px;">
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600;">
                1. While placing your second last card, choose whether to indicate that you have one card left to the group or not by stating “Solo!”
            </p>
            <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-muted); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; list-style-type: disc;">
                <li>While it is common courtesy to announce your last Card, I am not forcing a Rule to do so. Therefore, you are encouraged to use the tactic of hiding this information.</li>
                <li>However, if you do not and another Player notices before the next Player plays or Draws a Card, they can still call you out on it by saying “Solo!”. If they do, you must Draw 2 Cards to yourself.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- RULE 2 -->
        <div style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; padding-bottom: 15px;">
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600;">
                2. Possessing no cards at the end of your turn.
            </p>
            <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-muted); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; list-style-type: disc;">
                <li>If at the end of your turn you still have no Cards, the game ends and you win!</li>
                <li>Points can be scored if desired [see: Scoring], and play can restart if desired.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- RULE 3 -->
        <div style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px;">
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600;">
                3. If the last card played in a round has a Draw or Deal Effect, continue play until someone is forced to Draw cards.
            </p>
            <ul style="margin: 0 0 12px 0; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-muted); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; list-style-type: disc;">
                <li>Someone must Draw from the last Draw or Deal Effect Card. Until that happens, your Win is not guaranteed...</li>
                <li>If you play a Draw or Deal Effect Card as your last Card and a Player/s Respond in Kind, and in doing so, brings the Draw or Deal Effect back to you, with nothing to defend yourself with you must bear the consequences of the Draw or Deal Effect you initiated, cancelling your Win.</li>
            </ul>
            <div class="note-box">
                <strong>NOTE:</strong> There is also the possibility of the Drawer obtaining Anti-Fun for example, that can still be used to negate your Win. It is also a possibility that while Drawing with certain Expansions that a Group Targeting Draw Effect Chaos Card could charge everyone, including you, Card/s that would also cancel your win.
            </div>
        </div>
 	
        <!-- RULE 4 -->
        <div style="margin: 0; padding-bottom: 15px;">
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600;">
                4. Special Victory Conditions.
            </p>
            <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-muted); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; list-style-type: disc;">
                <li>Some Expansions have Special Victory Conditions that exceed the normal means of Winning. For example:
                    <ul style="padding-left: 20px; list-style-type: circle; margin-top: 4px;">
                        <li>The Singularity Expansion allows you to collect all 3 Unification Class Chaos Cards.</li>
                        <li>While the Crisis Expansion’s Crisis Class Chaos Cards allow for many different Special Victory Conditions.</li>
                        <li>Finally, the Cataclysm Expansion allows you to collect all 6 Ancient Stone Class Chaos Cards.</li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
                <li>In any of these situations, doing so automatically, and instantly, Wins you the Game!</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- RULE 5 -->
        <div style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px;">
            <p style="margin: 0 0 10px 0; font-size: 1rem; font-weight: 600;">
                5. The game ends Without a Clear Winner.
            </p>
            <ul style="margin: 0 0 12px 0; padding-left: 20px; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary); display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 8px; list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                <li>As stated in Universal Game Notes: Important Notes: Rule 1, the Deck could run out of Drawable Cards.</li>
                <li>The Doomsday Expansion has the Soloversal Destruction Chaos Card that can cause Everyone to lose.</li>
                <li>In any situation without a clear Winner:
                    <ul style="padding-left: 20px; list-style-type: disc; margin-top: 4px; color: var(--text-muted);">
                        <li>The Player with the least number of Cards Wins.<br />
                        <span style="font-size: 0.88rem; font-style: italic;">If Scoring, do so normally [but do not count your own Cards].</span></li>
                        <li>If more than one Player has equal Cards to Win, They Draw.<br />
                        <span style="font-size: 0.88rem; font-style: italic;">If Scoring, count the other winning Player’s Cards as well [but not your own].</span></li>
                    </ul>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: right; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
        <a href="#top" style="color: var(--color-link); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700;">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>	

    <!-- TEAM GAMEPLAY -->
    <h2 id="team-gameplay">TEAM GAMEPLAY:</h2>
    <div class="rules-box">
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1rem;">
            1. Make Teams with an even number of Members.
        </p>
        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            2. Choose the Turn Order for Teams &amp; Members [alternating Teams/Members between turns (e.g.: Team 1: Member 1, Team 2: Member 1, Team 1: Member 2, Team 2: Member 2, etc) ].
        </p>
        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            3. Reorganise Seating arrangements to Match Team &amp; Member Turns.
        </p>
        <div style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px;">
            <p style="margin: 0 0 12px 0; font-size: 1rem;">
                4. Next, choose which Victory Condition to use before beginning play:
            </p>
            
            <div style="margin-bottom: 15px; padding-left: 10px; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);">
                <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">OPTION 1: Relaxed:</strong>
                <p style="margin: 0 0 6px 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">• The First Member to get rid of all their Cards wins for their Team.</p>
                <div class="note-box" style="margin-top: 5px; padding: 8px 12px;">
                    <strong>NOTE:</strong> If Scoring, do not count your Team Member’s Cards.
                </div>
            </div>

            <div style="padding-left: 10px; border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);">
                <strong style="color: var(--text-primary); display: block; margin-bottom: 4px;">OPTION 2: Competitive:</strong>
                <p style="margin: 0 0 6px 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">• The first Team with All Members to get rid of all their Cards Wins.</p>
                <div class="note-box" style="margin-top: 5px; padding: 8px 12px;">
                    <strong>NOTES:</strong> Team Members with no Cards left can only be Group Targeted [e.g.: United We Fall]; this includes Group Targeting Trap Class Chaos Cards [e.g.: Epidemic from the Contagion Expansion]. Otherwise, Team Members with no Cards are Removed from the Game and have their Turns Automatically Skipped. If they receive Cards again, they are Re-added to the Game.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            5. Follow all other Game Rules.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: right; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
        <a href="#top" style="color: var(--color-link); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700;">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>


    <!-- TEAM GAMEPLAY: TRADING -->
    <h2 id="team-trading">TEAM GAMEPLAY: TRADING:</h2>
    <div class="rules-box">
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1rem;">
            1. 2 Team Members can Trade Cards [a free Card Swapping Effect] at a 1:1 Ratio on their Member Turn, by saying “Team Trade Requested.” However, this can only do so a minimum of once every 2 Team Turns, regardless of which Team Member took said Team Turns.
        </p>
        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            2. All Card Types are allowed to be Traded during a Team Trade. This includes Trading for a Counter Class Chaos Card when facing Draw Effects [Stacked or otherwise].
        </p>
        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            3. If there are more than 2 Players in a Team, the initiating Trader must designate which Team Member will participate.
        </p>
        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            4. Discussion of which Cards are wanted to be received or be given in return is Forbidden. You must trust your Team Member to help however they can.
        </p>
        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            5. Once a Team Trade is Requested, that 1:1 Trade Must be done [regardless of if the Traded Card would end up being helpful or not].
        </p>
        <p style="margin: 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--text-divider); padding-top: 15px; font-size: 1rem;">
            6. Finally, a Team Member does not have to use the Card that was Traded to them on that Member’s Turn if they do not want to.
        </p>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: right; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
        <a href="#top" style="color: var(--color-link); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700;">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>


    <!-- TEAM GAMEPLAY: SPECIAL VICTORY CONDITIONS -->
    <h2 id="team-victory-changes">TEAM GAMEPLAY: SPECIAL VICTORY CONDITIONS CHANGES:</h2>
    <div class="rules-box">
        <p style="margin: 0 0 4px 0; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary);">Singularity Expansion:</p>
        <ul style="margin: 0 0 15px 0; padding-left: 20px; list-style-type: disc; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem;">
            <li>A Team wins if they possess all 3 Unification Class Chaos Cards between any of their Team Members.</li>
        </ul>

        <p style="margin: 0 0 4px 0; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary);">Crisis Expansion:</p>
        <ul style="margin: 0 0 15px 0; padding-left: 20px; list-style-type: disc; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem;">
            <li>Crisis Trap Class Chaos Cards are totalled for the Team.</li>
        </ul>

        <p style="margin: 0 0 4px 0; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary);">Cataclysm Expansion:</p>
        <ul style="margin: 0; padding-left: 20px; list-style-type: disc; color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 0.95rem;">
            <li>The Bulk Possession Notes and Special Victory Condition are not shared across Team Members. However, on any Team Member’s Playable Turn, 1 Ancient Stone CAN be given to any other Team Member if all Team Members agree to Deal 5 Cards to themselves each [in play order]. Discussion of which Ancient Stone is given and who gets it is allowed by Team Members if it is kept brief.</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div style="text-align: right; margin-top: 10px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
        <a href="#top" style="color: var(--color-link); text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.88rem; font-weight: 700;">🔝 Return to Index Matrix</a>
    </div>


    <!-- SCORING -->
    <h2 id="scoring">SCORING:</h2>
    <div class="rules-box">
        <p style="margin: 0; font-style: italic; color: var(--text-muted);">
            • If you feel up to it, mix things up by tracking your progress by accumulating your score as rounds progress.
        </p>
        <p style="margin: 15px 0; font-size: 1rem;">
            • The first Player to get rid of all their Cards in a round receives points for all Cards left in their opponent’s Hands as follows:
        </p>

        <div style="overflow-x: auto; margin: 15px 0; border: 1px solid var(--text-divider); border-radius: 8px;">
            <table style="width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; text-align: left; font-size: 0.95rem;">
                <thead>
                    <tr style="background: var(--bg-main-box); border-bottom: 2px solid var(--text-divider);">
                        <th style="padding: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary);">Card Type</th>
                        <th style="padding: 12px; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary);">Point Value</th>
                    </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
